<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 03 at 4:42AM CDT  by NWS Mobile</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Monroe,
northeastern Washington and central Clarke Counties through 530 AM
CDT...
At 442 AM CDT, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated a
strong thunderstorm near Wagarville, or 10 miles southeast of Chatom,
moving northeast at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Jackson, Grove Hill, Saint Stephens, Wagarville, Leroy, Whatley and
Fulton.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
